1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:09,400
Prediction markets say one thing, opinion polls say another,
and the news says something entirely different.

2
00:00:09,700 --> 00:00:16,700
AFOS Analytics is the first open-source platform
that cross-references all three — in real time, side by side.

3
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:26,000
Right now we're tracking Brazil's 2026 presidential election,
with 14 more countries on the global map.

4
00:00:26,300 --> 00:00:32,800
Every 30 minutes, the platform pulls live odds
from the world's largest prediction market.

5
00:00:33,100 --> 00:00:39,500
It cross-references 200+ electoral polls registered with TSE,
from over 17 institutes.

6
00:00:39,800 --> 00:00:45,000
And aggregates hundreds of headlines,
auto-categorized by topic.

7
00:00:45,300 --> 00:00:51,700
Everything is free. Everything is open-source.
No login, no tracking, no paywall.

8
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:59,100
Built by a solo founder in Brazil, because electoral transparency
shouldn't be the monopoly of polling institutes.

9
00:00:59,400 --> 00:01:05,500
If you care about how political risk is priced,
measured, and narrated — take a look.

10
00:01:05,800 --> 00:01:12,000
AFOS Analytics has no ideological or partisan affiliation.
It only observes what the data shows.

11
00:01:12,300 --> 00:01:16,700
Link in the description. Star us on GitHub.
